- root fact = the matching-factor transport: `(Y′ − C w) ∣ R ⟹ (Y′ − C (aPDecoded w)) ∣ f_z` (two `map_dvd` steps);
- order-0 congruence = the base-point fact `w(x₀, z) = t_z`, with `π_z(βHensel 0) = t_z` proven (`pi_z_βHensel_zero` — the recursion base reads the branch value);
- index-`t` vanishing = the Prop-5.5 degree bound `w.natDegree < k`, read at the place;
- separability = `R.Separable` (existing transport).

**Capstones:** `mpFin_of_decoded` (the exact `mpFin`/`mpPoint` family shape every §5 bundle consumes) and — composing with `HvanishSupply` + `GenuineTruncationFin` — **`gammaGenuine_eq_trunc_of_decoded`: the Claim 5.8′ truncation identity end-to-end** from: `(Y′ − C w) ∣ R`, `w.natDegree < k`, per-place base-point roots, per-place ξ-nonvanishing, `R.Separable`, the genuine representative `hrepG`, discriminant counting, and the graded side conditions. Every hypothesis is a named, finitely-checkable GS-side fact; **no per-`t` cargo remains anywhere on the truncation lane**.

Remaining on this lane: (1) the surface factor `(Y′ − C w) ∣ R` itself (GS/Prop-5.5 matching content — `RationalRootSupply`/`MatchingExtractor` feed it), (2) base-point root production (`RationalRootSupply.rationalRoot_of_matching_branch` gives exactly these), (3) the ξ-nonvanishing certificate (disc-product lane), (4) `hrepG` (wave-4 satisfiability check in flight).

