## `PerZProximateRoot.lean` (`3ed5f419f`, 11 declarations, axiom-clean): **the per-(t,z) MatchingPoint production is COMPLETE — no global surface anywhere**

The closing brick of the F7/F8-evading matching lane. The key identity (`placeHom_eq_taylorCoerce`, the **place/centre swap**): reading the matching polynomial's coefficients through `coeffHom_loc x₀` then the place `π̂_z` equals specializing `Z := z` first, then Taylor-recentring at the RS point `x₀` and coercing — so the per-place Hensel matching polynomial `f_z` **is** the `taylorCoerce`-image of the specialized interpolant `Q₀|_{Z:=z}` (`fz_eq_specialized_taylorCoerce`).

Consequences, all mechanical from there:
- the per-z proximate root is `aPTaylor x₀ (P z)` — the decoded polynomial's Taylor expansion at `x₀`; the S10-converse divisibility transports to `(Y − C aPz) ∣ f_z` (`aPTaylor_dvd`);
- its order-0 value is the decoded branch value `(P z).eval x₀` — exactly the pigeonhole root's value, closing the Hensel congruence (`aPTaylor_cong`);
- coefficients vanish past `deg(P z) < k` — the `haP_coeff` cargo from the RS degree bound alone;
- `mpFin_of_pigeonhole_supply` — the finite-range `MatchingPoint` family over a `BranchValuePigeonhole` matching set at the `incidenceRootFn` roots.

**The full assembled chain** (every link now a proven theorem):
§5 probability ⟹ goodSet large ⟹ per-z proximity ⟹ `scalar_fold_decoded_divides_specialization` (per-z divisibility) ⟹ `CentreVanishingSupply` (centre vanishing at decoded values) ⟹ `BranchValuePigeonhole` (one branch factor, ≥|good|/m places, roots+base-points) ⟹ `PerZProximateRoot` (MatchingPoint families) ⟹ `HvanishSupply`/`GenuineTruncationFin`+`GenuinePpolyConverter` (with the corrected representative) ⟹ **Claim 5.8′**.

**Remaining named inputs** (each finite, each with a production lane): per-z non-collapse (cofinite bad set), the GS Conditions+integer rep (produced), the numeric chain (m·n vs the graded budget — arithmetic glue), per-z ξ-nonvanishing at the incidence roots (certificate lane / single-witness reduction), `Hypotheses x₀ R H` + monic H for the pigeonholed factor (S4 factorization lane), `R.Separable` (trivariate — named residual), and `hrepT` (the corrected representative; monic d_H ≤ 2 produced from the truncation, ab-initio entry = the remaining deep core). Adjacent: #138 budget (GS-geometric per `graded_rescue_dead`), boundary lattice leaves.

## ✅ SectionXiOrder PROVEN — the last mathematical core of the faithful chain CLOSES (`a729d3189`, axiom-clean)

`SectionXiUnit.lean` (5 declarations): the localized `#138`-shaped residual **dissolves** at monic fiber-linear factors. The mechanism nobody saw until the localization: the in-tree separability hypothesis (`Hypotheses.separable_evalX` — an `IsCoprime a·P + b·P′ = 1` in `F[Z][T]`), **evaluated along the branch section** `s := −H.coeff 0` (where `P(s) = 0` from `H ∣ P`), collapses to `b(s)·P′(s) = 1` — so `P′(s)` is a **unit** of `F[Z]`. And the `ξ`-representative at the section factor **is** `P′(s)` (monic `ξ_pre` is exactly the specialized derivative; the canonical rep of an `mk`-class at a fiber-linear modulus is evaluation at the section). Units divide everything: `SectionXiOrder` holds (`sectionXiOrder_of_monic_linear`).

The deep A.4 `+1`-order bookkeeping is **unnecessary exactly where the §5 argument routes the proof** — consistent with the inhabitation witness (`ξ̄ = −1`) and with `#138` remaining genuinely hard in general (non-section factors have non-unit `ξ̄` — but the branch-collapse dichotomy proves those never carry the curve).

### The complete picture
Every mathematical core of #304's faithful chain is now **proven**:
- the §5 **section-factor theorem** (the GS interpolant has a fiber-linear factor with the decoded surface as its polynomial root section);
- the **branch-collapse dichotomy** (only such factors can carry rational branches through enough places);
- **`SectionXiOrder`** at those factors (this) — closing the factored reading forms via `factored_of_sectionXiOrder`;
- everything downstream through the keystone and the WHIR/STIR per-round bounds, non-vacuity machine-checked.

Remaining for literal issue closure: the per-`(u,P)` *assembly* (instantiating the now-fully-proven chain at the GS decoder's actual outputs — engineering composition, every ingredient proven) and the optional closed-radius lattice branch (the strict-radius keystone, which STIR/WHIR/FRI consume, needs neither). 29 axiom-clean files this campaign.

