## ⚠️ FINDING + REPAIR: the per-place cargo was Taylor-transposed — faithful front door landed (`GSSurfaceTaylorRepair.lean`, axiom-clean)

**The finding (F-series, statement-level).** The matching polynomial `f z = (R.map (coeffHom_loc x₀)).map (π̂_z)` is built through `taylorAlgHom (C x₀)`: its series coordinate is the **domain variable recentred at x₀**. The faithful decoded root is therefore the Taylor coercion `aPTaylor x₀ (P z) = ↑(taylor x₀ (P z))` — exactly what the matching lane (`PerZProximateRoot.aPTaylor_dvd`) produces — **not** the plain coercion `↑(P z)` appearing in the `hdvd`/`hcong` fields of `curveFamilyData_of_truncatedLocalRoot` and `GSSurfaceData`. The plain-coercion fields are instantiable only at recentring-invariant families; the non-vacuity witness (constants) did not discriminate the two coordinates. Same bug class as the three machine-refuted keystone surfaces — caught this time by tracing the producer lane against the consumer field.

**The repair (mechanical, no re-proving).** Taylor cargo for `P` **is** plain cargo for the shifted family `z ↦ taylor x₀ (P z)`:
* `aPTaylor_eq_coe` — the proximate root IS the plain coercion of the shifted polynomial;
* `hdvdP_of_matching` / `hcong_of_branch_value` — the shifted bundle's per-place fields are the matching-lane outputs **verbatim** (so `GSSurfaceData` at the shifted family is instantiable from S10-converse divisibilities + decoded branch values);
* `taylor_comp_sub` + `curveFamilyData_comp_shift` — `CurveFamilyData` transports back through `X ↦ X − s` (coefficients `c_t ∘ (X − C s)`, same `n`, same curve centre);
* **`correlatedAgreement_affine_curves_of_GS_surface_taylor`** — the faithful keystone front door: `δ_ε_correlatedAgreementCurves` at every `δ < 1 − √ρ` from a per-`(u,P)` producer of `(s, GSSurfaceData u (taylor s ∘ P))` — the exact shape the GS matching lane instantiates.

Also landed this hour: `GSSurfaceHtailPigeonhole.lean` — `htail` produced from the pigeonhole matching lane (the Claim-5.8′ ab-initio capstone at the section divisor, where monicity + positive degree + per-place ξ-nonvanishing are all structural).

**Score for the bundle fields**: `v, hdvd, Hypotheses` ✓ produced (SectionFromSurface) · `htail` ✓ produced (two routes) · `hdvdP/hcong` ✓ produced at the faithful (shifted) family (this file) · `hdegc` → Claim-5.8 weight shape (GSSurfaceDegSupply) · `hsepR` = known-open `SurfaceSeparabilitySupply` · numerics (window/budget/count) = per-instance GS accounting.

