- **Capstones**: `interpolatedRep_hrep_hdegX` (:449) and `exists_representative_pair` (:481) — the bundle's terminal per-`P` field pair `(hrep, hdegX, natDegree < #s)` **exists**, produced from: per-z vanishing of the cleared differences (`hvan` — the matching-lane per-z currency), loose weight bounds (`hw` — dischargeable through `weight_betaRec_sub_clearedCoeff_le` + `betaRec_weight_le_graded`), one §6 counting-set largeness (`hcard`), ξ-nonvanishing, and the in-tree `htail` content.

Two design notes recorded in the file header: (i) the producer targets `gammaLocal` (the `hrep`-against-`gammaGenuine` shape is unsatisfiable at `d_H ≥ 2` — finding F6, `GenuinePpolyConverter.not_hrepG_of_two_le_natDegree`); (ii) nothing here consumes the sharp budget — every weight input is the proven graded one.

**Frontier consequence**: the bundle's last per-`P` field pair is now produced, conditional only on currencies the matching lane already outputs. The remaining #304 work is wiring `hvan`/`hw`/`hcard` from the assembled GS matching lane (per-z proximate roots → cleared-coefficient vanishing) into these capstones — plumbing in the lane's existing currency, no new mathematics identified.

